{
  "explanation": "The defendant committed a serious breach of fiduciary duty by embezzling funds from their employer. While the amount of twenty-five thousand dollars is substantial, the defendant has shown remorse through partial restitution and has no prior criminal record. Balancing the need for deterrence and accountability with the mitigating factors of a clean history and ongoing repayment, a short period of incarceration is appropriate to emphasize the severity of the breach of trust without derailing the defendant's ability to eventually re-enter the workforce and complete restitution.",
  "verdict": 6
}
